### Health check (no auth)
GET http://localhost:8080/health

###

### Register a new user
POST http://localhost:8080/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Akshad Jaiswal",
  "email": "akshad@example.com",
  "password": "password123"
}

###

### Register — duplicate email (should return 409)
POST http://localhost:8080/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Duplicate",
  "email": "akshad@example.com",
  "password": "password123"
}

###

### Login — get JWT token
POST http://localhost:8080/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "akshad@example.com",
  "password": "password123"
}

###

### Login — wrong password (should return 401)
POST http://localhost:8080/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "akshad@example.com",
  "password": "wrongpassword"
}

###

### List users — no token (should return 401)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/v1/users

###

### List users — invalid token (should return 401)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/v1/users
Authorization: Bearer invalid.token.here

###

### List users — valid token (copy token from login response)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/v1/users
Authorization: Bearer PASTE_TOKEN_HERE

###

### Create user — valid token
POST http://localhost:8080/api/v1/users
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer PASTE_TOKEN_HERE

{
  "name": "Ketaki",
  "email": "ketaki@example.com"
}
